<!DOCTYPE html> 
<html>
  <head> 
    <title> 
      Connect To Vimeo
    </title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="/static/css/pre-connect-popup.css" media="screen" />
    <script>
	function next()
	{
		window.location='${params.next}';
	}

	</script>
  </head> 
<body> 
<div id="message">
	<div class='pre-connect-popup'>
	<div class='header-bar'>Connecting...</div>
	
	<div class='popup-text'> 
		<p>Sparkwise will now connect to your Vimeo account.
		Make sure the Vimeo account you are currently logged in to is the one you want to connect. 
		What happens if you connect to the wrong account? No big deal. Just remove it in the Sparkwise Connections window and start over.</p>
	
		<a href='javascript: next();' class='standard-button'>Continue</a>
		<a href='javascript:self.close()' class='standard-button'>Cancel</a>
	</div>
	<img  src="http://vimeo.com/log_out" style="width:0px;height:0px;"/>				   
</div>
</div>	
</body> 
</html>
